All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, List<E>, RandomAccess
public class CachedVector<E>
extends Vector<E>

This is a fast access Vector that sacrifices memory for speed. It will reduce the speed of indexOf method from O(n) to O(1). However it will at least double the memory used by Vector. So use it approriately.

Just like Vector, this implementation is synchronized. In comparision, CachedArrayList is not synchronized.

Adjusts the cache so that all values that are greater than index will increase by the value specified by the increase parameter.

Parameters:
index - the index. All values above this index will be changed.
increase - a positive number to increase or a negative number to decrease.
